We recommended that Management:

Require the Municipal Accountant to effect immediately the necessary adjustments relative to the book reconciling items with available supporting documents;

Instruct the Municipal Accountant to exert extra effort in locating the documents relative to prior years reconciling items and ensure that book reconciling items will not increase in the succeeding years;

Revert back to the CIB-LCCA the amount of all the stale checks of the Municipality and recognize the corresponding liability account or the government equity account whichever is applicable;

Communicate to the concerned depository bank regarding the bank errors presented in the Bank Reconciliation Statements (BRS) in order to arrive at the correct balance of the CIB-LCCA; and

Prepare the individual BRS for each depository account of the LGU.

We recommended that Management:

Stop the granting of additional cash advance to officials and employees unless settlement/liquidation of the previous cash advances was made;

Send demand letters to all accountable officers concerned to liquidate/settle immediately their cash advances. Copy of the said demand letters bearing the receipts of the concerned accountable officials/employees should be furnished the Audit Team;

Withhold the payment of any money due to accountable officers in case of failure to settle the cash advances despite demand as provided by law; and

Exhaust all means to locate the necessary supporting documents relative to the long outstanding cash advances.

We also recommend that cash advances of former officials and employees who are now deceased or cannot be located in which the Municipality’s effort to collect or settle is futile be requested to be written off in accordance with COA Circular No. 2016-005. Further, Management should avail all of the legal remedies in order for the concerned Municipal officials and employees to liquidate their outstanding cash advance.

